<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03837</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A UNIFIED HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT FUND AND A CENTRALIZED HOME FINANCING PROGRAM, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 7835, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "COMPREHENSIVE AND INTEGRATED SHELTER FINANCING ACT (CISFA) OF 1994"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to amend key provisions of RA 7835 or the Comprehensive and Integrated Shelter Finance Act (CISFA) of 1994 to establish, among others, a Unified Housing and Urban Development Fund to make long-term and affordable financing for housing purposes accessible for qualified low-income earners in need of a home of their own even they are not members of the SSS, GSIS of the Pag-IBIG Fund.

Further aims to establish a Centralized Home Financing Program that shall be sourced out by tapping key fund sources already been identified by law: among them, RA 7835 or CISFA, RA8282 or the amended SSS charter, RA8291 of the amended GSIS Charter and RA9679 of the new Pag-IBIG Fund Charter.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “CISFA  Amendments of 2017.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMUALDEZ, FERDINAND MARTIN G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-08-13</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Olivarez (000 2019-11-18)</td><td>2. Benitez (000 2020-02-11)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT ON 2019-08-20</td></tr></table>